# 📱 GeoVerify — Android App Setup Guide

Your React web app is now wrapped in a native Android shell using **Capacitor**. Here's everything you need to know.

---

## Architecture

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[React + Vite Web App] -->|npm run build| B[dist/ folder]
    B -->|npx cap sync| C[Android WebView Shell]
    C -->|Android Studio| D[APK / AAB]
```

> [!NOTE]
> Capacitor wraps your existing web app inside a native Android `WebView`. Your React code runs as-is — no rewrite needed. Native plugins (GPS, camera, haptics) are accessed via JavaScript bridges.

