## Prerequisites

Before opening in Android Studio, make sure you have:

1. **Android Studio** (latest stable) — [Download here](https://developer.android.com/studio)
2. **Java JDK 17+** — Android Studio usually bundles this
3. **Android SDK** — API level 33+ (installed via Android Studio SDK Manager)

---

## Quick Start Commands

### One-Command Build & Open

```bash
cd frontend
npm run android
```

This runs: `build → sync → open Android Studio`

### Individual Steps

```bash
# 1. Build the web app
npm run build

# 2. Sync web assets + plugins to Android
npm run cap:sync

# 3. Open in Android Studio
npm run cap:open
```

---

## Building the APK / AAB

### Debug APK (for testing)

1. Open the `frontend/android` folder in Android Studio
2. Wait for Gradle sync to complete (first time takes ~5 mins)
3. Connect your Android phone via USB (enable Developer Options + USB Debugging)
4. Click the green **▶ Run** button
5. Select your device → app installs and launches!

### Release AAB (for Play Store)

1. In Android Studio: **Build → Generate Signed Bundle / APK**
2. Choose **Android App Bundle**
3. Create or select your signing keystore
4. Build the release bundle

---

## Android Permissions Configured

| Permission | Why |
|---|---|
| `INTERNET` | API calls to Supabase backend |
| `ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION` | Geo-verified attendance check-in |
| `ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION` | Fallback location |
| `ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE` | Connectivity checks |
| `CAMERA` | Future: QR scan / selfie check-in |
| `VIBRATE` | Haptic feedback on actions |

---

## Native Features Enabled

| Plugin | Functionality |
|---|---|
| `@capacitor/status-bar` | Dark immersive status bar matching app theme |
| `@capacitor/keyboard` | Pushes content up when keyboard opens |
| `@capacitor/app` | Android back button → browser history navigation |
| `@capacitor/splash-screen` | Dark branded splash during app load |
| `@capacitor/geolocation` | Native GPS for attendance verification |
| `@capacitor/haptics` | Tactile feedback on button presses |

---

## Development Workflow

### Making Changes

```bash
# 1. Edit your React code normally
# 2. Rebuild
npm run build

# 3. Sync changes to Android
npx cap sync android

# 4. Re-run in Android Studio (▶ button)
```

### Live Reload (during development)

Edit `capacitor.config.ts` and add a server URL:

```typescript
server: {
  url: 'http://YOUR_PC_IP:5173',  // Your Vite dev server
  cleartext: true,
}
```

> [!WARNING]
> Remove the `server.url` before building for production! It's only for development.

---

## Troubleshooting

| Issue | Fix |
|---|---|
| Gradle sync fails | File → Invalidate Caches → Restart Android Studio |
| White screen on launch | Run `npx cap sync` — web assets may not have copied |
| Location not working | Check device permissions in Settings → Apps → GeoVerify |
| API calls failing | Ensure `VITE_API_BASE_URL` points to your deployed backend (not localhost) |
| Build error "SDK not found" | Set `ANDROID_HOME` env variable or update `local.properties` |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> For production builds, update `.env` to point `VITE_API_BASE_URL` to your deployed backend URL instead of `http://localhost:8000`.
